    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Auxiliary Rear Bearing Assembly</title>
        <para>Place the rear bearing cone over the bearing and into the rear bore. Align the .100 shim over the cone and
            install the rear bearing cover with 4 bolts. Tighten only until snug (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13027i0">left, Figure 180</hotlnk>). Retaining straps may also be used at this time; they
            are required for horizontal installation. Complete assembly by installing the remaining rear bearing cover (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13027i0">right, Figure 180</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f13027i0" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13027i0" filename="../figg13/G13027i0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 180. Align Shim Over Cone and Install Rear Bearing Covers</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcsubproc>
